                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="nastaliq" medium="ink">Persian copied in a good nasta’liq hand in black ink. Arabic in ‘naskh’ in red ink. Rubrication in red. 
                        The spine suggests that the name of the scribe is <persName>Vilāyat</persName></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>
                        Plain binding of red leather. Spine reads ترجمۀ فرج بعد از شدت بخط ولایت
                     </p>
                     <decoNote type="illustration"/>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <accMat>
                     <stamp>
                        f.1a Seal reading Abū l-Muḥassin 1283 AH 
                     </stamp>
                     <note>
                        f1. Note: f.i ‘Furj [sic.] bad az shiddat – ‘pleasure after pain’. Translated from an Arabic work now lost – a highly balanced and outstanding work – written in Persian’. 
                     </note>
                  </accMat>
